        "summary": "A 50-vendor fashion marketplace achieved remarkable success by creating the region's first fully virtual shopping mall.",
        "description": "## The Challenge\n\nCairo Fashion Hub wanted to create a unified online presence for 50+ independent fashion vendors. Each vendor had different levels of digital capability, and creating individual e-commerce stores would be expensive and fragmented.\n\n## The Solution\n\nArabiq designed and built a complete virtual mall experience. Each vendor received their own branded virtual storefront within a cohesive mall environment. Shoppers could walk through the mall, browse different stores, and checkout from multiple vendors in a single transaction.\n\nWe implemented:\n- Individual vendor dashboards for inventory management\n- Unified checkout with split payments to vendors\n- Arabic AI chatbot for customer assistance\n- Gamification to encourage exploration\n\n## The Results\n\n- **$2.1M in sales** in the first year\n- **200% increase** in daily visitors compared to physical location\n- **60% cost savings** for vendors vs. individual e-commerce stores\n- **35 new vendors** joined after seeing initial success\n\n## Client Testimonial\n\n\"The virtual mall concept was revolutionary for our vendors. Small boutiques that could never afford their own e-commerce presence now have beautiful virtual stores that look as good as the big brands.\" — Yasmine Fouad, Founder, Cairo Fashion Hub",
